details:
Case 119 is a 55 year-old male Singapore Citizen who has no recent travel history to affected countries and regions.

He reported onset of symptoms on 27 February and had sought treatment at a general practitioner (GP) clinic on the same day, and on 29 February. He presented at the Urgent Care Centre at Alexandra Hospital on 1 March and 5 March. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 5 March afternoon.

Prior to hospital admission, he had mostly stayed at his home at Stirling Road. He is employed by SingTel but had not gone to work since onset of symptoms.
